b'RT @investmish: Companies whose products/services you love can be a great signal to invest in.\n\nTo me, Dropbox ( $DBX ) is one of those com\xe2\x80\xa6'

b"Here's the clincher. Last year $DBX jacked its prices up 20% from $99 to $120/yr. I didn't think about other options - because I couldn't. All my files are stored and organised on DBX. Migrating would be a headache. Guess I'm locked in. Sounds like a pretty good moat to me..(4/4)"

b"This got my attention because it

a) solved an issue I have
b) adds functionality and 
c) cleverly gets subscribers to market to non $DBX subcribers (network effect)

Now I don't own the stock, but it sparked my interest to have a closer look (2/4)"

b'Companies whose products/services you love can be a great signal to invest in.\n\nTo me, Dropbox ( $DBX ) is one of those companies.
